939th March, 1693—— Seventy Italians, whom the Muscovites had brought from Venice, were discharged without payment of their expenses. Notwithstand- ing the many inconveniences through which they had to retrace their long journey, none got more than ten roubleS, others nine, and others only eight. Ex- asperated at this injustice, they took the liberty of saying direful things of the whole Muscovite race.
